- `src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/corpus_harness.rs:145` does genuinely add a present-but-stale test, but it only locks the `doc_manifest_sha mismatch` return, not the `identity mismatch` return in [`tests/support/corpus_harness.rs:721`]( /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_harness.rs:721 ) and [`:728`]( /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_harness.rs:728 ). In `(1c)`, the sidecar’s identity fields are left intact and only `doc_manifest_sha` is tampered in place at [tests/corpus_harness.rs]( /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/corpus_harness.rs:160 ), so an isolated regression of the identity-mismatch check could still slip through green.

Answers to your checks:

- Yes, `(1c)` really does hit the present-but-stale path, not a cold/new-path miss. The second fixture rebuilds the same key from the same identity/label/doc set at [tests/support/corpus_harness.rs]( /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_harness.rs:520 )-[521], reads the same blob/meta paths at [522]( /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_harness.rs:522 )-[523], and because `fx_s2` is a fresh fixture it constructs a fresh `CachingEmbedder::load` at [435]( /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_harness.rs:435 )-[442]. With both files present, `read_cache` cannot take the cold path at [700]( /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_harness.rs:700 )-[701].
- The suite would go red if the `doc_manifest_sha` mismatch were regressed to silent fallback: `Ok(None)` would surface `"cold"` instead of `"mismatch"` via [529]( /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/support/corpus_harness.rs:529 )-[533], and `Ok(Some(_))` would make `embed_cache_hit` true. But it would not go red for an isolated regression of only the identity-mismatch check, because `(1c)` never creates an identity mismatch.
- I don’t see a new regression from the added test itself. It is isolated in its own temp cache dir, uses a fresh fixture instance for the reload, and the sidecar tamper is local to that tempdir.

